  [ Please discuss significant results or key outcomes for each relevant task, including major findings, developments, and/or conclusions. Include data/evidence that supports the impact of each task in the project’s progress. List each task individually. ],
  [ #strong[Task 1a:]] Modeling of Transducer Array for Uniform Ultrasound Delivery and Characterization of Ultrasound Transducers]#strong[Milestone 4:]]Milestone 4 was initially completed with the characterization of a 950 kHz ultrasound transducer from Acoustiic (ACT). This transducer, equipped with 4,608-channel integrated electronics, served as an effective stand-in to evaluate subsystem performance. Hydrophone measurements conducted at 903 kHz and 993 kHz using 25 V and 65 V inputs demonstrated strong acoustic performance, with pressure fields approaching -0.8 MPa. The system also supported a wide range of waveform parameters, including pulse durations from 20 µs to 4 ms and a duty cycle exceeding 64%. Simulation results closely matched experimental data, with alignment within ±15%. This interim testing validated key system functions and established a reliable predictive baseline for the future custom array.#emph[SonALAsense (SAS) originally submitted the Milestone 4 report on April 11, 2025. However, based on feedback from ARPA-H, the Milestone will be resubmitted once ACT completes the fabrication of the prototype transducer with the specified frequency. Since ACT is now a subcontractor, rather than a vendor, they had to wait to start the work on this milestone until they were approved by ARPA-H.] ACT was approved as a subcontractor on August 29, 2025, after which weekly coordination meetings between SAS and ACT were initiated to finalize the project plan and align on technical requirements, with particular focus on well plate and microfluidic testing. Following this coordination, ACT completed fabrication and hydrophone characterization of the custom transducer prototype, designated SN-550. Hydrophone testing began shortly after the hydrophone arrived on December 16, 2025. #underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[Once SAS received thea]]#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[A]]nalysis of the data and simulations#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ Milestone 4]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ was resubmitted ]]#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[  ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[on ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[January 24, 2026. ]]#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[is expected to be shared with SonALAsense by January 14, 2026.]]  #underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ARPA-H did provide follow up questions to the report that SAS were addressed via email]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[. ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ Milestone 4 w]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[as successfully submitted in the PMS system on February 2, 2026.]]The SN-550 transducer prototype #underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[was delivered ]]#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[is scheduled for delivery]] to the SonALAsense laboratory during the week of January 19, 2026.#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ On site training of SAS personnel was completed during the same week.]]  #strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[With hydrophone testing complete, the SonALAsense team is compiling the hydrophone measurement data and associated documentation and plans to resubmit the Milestone 4 report by the end of January 2026.]]#strong[Task 1b:]] Determination of PpIX Kinetics in Patient-derived Samples]#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[#strong[Milestone 5: ​]SAS has completed PpIX accumulation studies in all commercially available hematologic cancer cell lines. All cell lines demonstrated a dose- and time-dependent accumulation of PpIX, suggesting that all indications studied thus far represent viable candidates for PDT/SDT studies. The Milestone 5 report was initially prepared based on these results and additional supporting studies and was originally submitted on November 7, 2025.]]#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[Following this initial submission, ARPA-H provided questions on November 21, 2025, and SAS subsequently  submitted a revised Milestone 5 report on November 25, 2025. In early December 2025, ARPA-H provided additional feedback indicating that the results and conclusions should be more clearly and accurately stated in alignment with the data presented. These data interpretations were discussed jointly by the ARPA-H and SAS teams during the December 4, 2025, on-site meeting.]]#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[Taking ARPA-H’s guidance into account, SAS resubmitted the Milestone 5 report on December 15, 2025. Milestone 5 was conditionally approved on December 21, 2025, with ARPA-H adding additional conclusions regarding the level of CD45 marker correlation and observed PpIX accumulation trends. The finalized Milestone 5 report was successfully submitted in the PMS system on December 22, 2025.]]#highlight(fill: yellow.lighten(60%))[{]#footnote[preclinical team to update (by lenora henry)]#strong[Milestone 6:]}SAS #underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ has completed ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[dosing kinetics of PpIX accumulation ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[to establish differential ratio in commercial cancer cell lines, non-cancerous ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[(NCC) ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[PBMC ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[or ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[BMMCs, and patient derived PBMCs ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[or ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[BMMCs]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ across all six indicated leukemia indications. ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[All cell lines continue to demonstrate a dose and time-dependent escalation of PpIX accumulation]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[  relative to NCC PBMCs. This same differential however, was not observed]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ in comparison of treated NCC PBMC or BMMCs to patient-derived samples. ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[It is our belief this finding is due to the heterogenic nature of these sample types]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[,]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ and the]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ highly]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ variable nature of ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[blast and cancer cell populations found both across and within ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[indications when screening ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[patient derived samples]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ at ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[a small scale. The milestone 6 report was prepared based upon these findings and submitted on]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ April 7#super[th], 2026.]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[  ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[No requests for changes or amendments were provided by ARPA-H. ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[  ]]#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[anticipates completing Milestone 6 by mid-February 2026, enabling the procurement of additional normal (non-cancerous) PBMCs and human patient samples for testing and comparator studies as well as completion of the on-site training by ACT of the SN-550 device (scheduled for mid-January 2026).]]  #strong[Task 1c:]] Determination of Optimal Ultrasound Parameters for SDT Across Hematologic Malignancy Patient Samples]#highlight(fill: yellow.lighten(60%))[{]#footnote[sean &amp; ryan to update (by lenora henry)]#strong[Milestone 7:​]}#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[Completion of Milestone 7 is dependent on optimizing the ultrasound dose for #emph[in vitro] SDT-induced cell killing. Although Milestone 7 was originally scheduled for completion in November 2025, progress cannot be made until ACT provides the SDT device. According to ACT, device delivery is now expected in mid-January, with milestone completion anticipated approximately 6–8 weeks thereafter in April 2026.]]#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[The SAS Technical team is working with ACT, using feedback from the preclinical team, to optimize user needs for both PDT and SDT treatment of preclinical samples. The results from the SDT experiments will also contribute to the milestones in Task 2 on informing what ultrasound parameters are needed in order to stimulate cavitation in the ESDT millifluidic devices.  ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[SAS ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[received the device from ACT the week of January 19#super[th] , with installation and trai]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ning completed during that same time. ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[Determination of optimal ultrasound dose ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[has presented expected challenges that were being troubleshooted.]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[  ]]Despite rapid efforts since delivery to identify parameters necessary to induce death in commercial cell lines, testing to date has demonstrated an unreliability to kill cancer cells in the absence or presence of 5-ALA.#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[  ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[proved to be ]]]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[a ]]]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[far]]]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ more]]]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[  ]]#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[difficult]]]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ task than ]]]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[initially]]]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[#strike(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[ believed.]]  ]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[Associated c]]#underline(stroke: red)[#text(fill: red)[hallenges 